.TH "i915_perf_add_config_ioctl" 9 "i915_perf_add_config_ioctl" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
i915_perf_add_config_ioctl \- DRM ioctl() for userspace to add a new OA config
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" i915_perf_add_config_ioctl
.BI "(struct drm_device *dev "  ","
.BI "void *data "  ","
.BI "struct drm_file *file "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
drm device
.IP "data" 12
ioctl data (pointer to struct drm_i915_perf_oa_config) copied from
userspace (unvalidated)
.IP "file" 12
drm file
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Validates the submitted OA register to be saved into a new OA config that
can then be used for programming the OA unit and its NOA network.
.SH "RETURN"
A new allocated config number to be used with the perf open ioctl
or a negative error code on failure.
